  <div class="information-block">
    <h2 class="buttface"><strong>Travel, Accomodation & Parking:</strong></h1><br>
    <h4 class="buttfaceT">Travel:</h4>
    <h5 class="buttface">The closest stations are Chichester, Bosham & Fishbourne. Trains to Chichester are most regular and it is a 15 minute drive to the Church from there. There is a taxi rank outside of the main entrance to the station (on the other side of the track if you're coming from London) </h5>
    <h4 class="buttfaceT">Accomodation:</h4>
    <h5 class="buttface">There are some hotels and B&Bs in Bosham, such as the Millstream or the Bosham Inn. For a wider range of options try Chichester, where there is a Travelodge and a Premier Inn.</h5><br>
    <h4 class="buttfaceT">Parking:</h4>
    <h5 class="buttface">The best place to park on the day is Bosham car park, which is a couple of minutes walk from the church. If you will be driving straight home from the reception, let us know in advance & we'll find you a space on Smugglers Lane nearby.</h5>
